{"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"categoryPathComponent":"MeetSwiftUITheming","role":"project","category":"SwiftUI Theming","title":"Change themes at runtime"},"kind":"project","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/dev.alexanderweiss.swiftui_theming\/tutorials\/SwiftUITheming\/02-01-ChangeThemesAtRuntime"},"sections":[{"title":"Change themes at runtime","kind":"hero","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to dynamically change themes at runtime."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"estimatedTimeInMinutes":15,"chapter":"Advanced"},{"tasks":[{"contentSection":[{"kind":"fullWidth","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Before enabling theme changes at runtime, you need a mechanism to trigger the change. This tutorial assumes the change is user-driven through a UI. However, themes can also be changed programmatically without a UI.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"anchor":"Create-a-view-to-change-the-theme","title":"Create a view to change the theme","stepsSection":[{"media":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a file named "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ThemeChangerView.swift"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"caption":[],"type":"step","code":"02-01-01-code-0001.swift","runtimePreview":null},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Access the "},{"code":"ThemeManager","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance from the environment."}]}],"code":"02-01-01-code-0002.swift","type":"step","media":null,"runtimePreview":null,"caption":[]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the view’s body, create a binding to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ThemeManager"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":"02-01-01-code-0003.swift","type":"step","media":null,"runtimePreview":null,"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is required because ","type":"text"},{"code":"ThemeManager","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is marked as an "},{"code":"@Observable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" type."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"media":null,"code":"02-01-01-code-0004.swift","runtimePreview":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Next, add the basic structure of the view. In this case, use a simple "},{"code":"Form","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" containing a single entry for a picker, allowing the user to select a theme."}]}],"caption":[],"type":"step"},{"code":"02-01-01-code-0005.swift","caption":[{"name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For this implementation, ensure you have multiple themes defined in your app and their types are accessible to the module where your theme changer view is located."}]}],"style":"note"}],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Implement the picker as you would any other picker in SwiftUI. Since ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Theme"},{"type":"text","text":" instances conform to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"type":"text","text":", they can be directly used in the "},{"code":"tag","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier. Additionally, use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Bindable"},{"type":"text","text":" to link the picker’s selection directly to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"selectedTheme"},{"type":"text","text":" property of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ThemeManager"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]}],"media":null,"runtimePreview":null,"type":"step"},{"media":"02-01-01-video-0001-swiftui-theming-demo.mp4","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This implementation provides users with an interface to change themes at runtime. Feel free to enhance it further and create a more visually appealing theme picker using the techniques outlined here."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step","caption":[],"runtimePreview":null,"code